						               													<description>&amp;#208;&amp;#162;&amp;#209;&amp;#131;&amp;#209;&amp;#128;&amp;#208;&amp;#189;&amp;#208;&amp;#184;&amp;#209;&amp;#128; &amp;#208;&amp;#146;&amp;#208;&amp;#190;&amp;#208;&amp;#187;&amp;#209;&amp;#136;&amp;#208;&amp;#181;&amp;#208;&amp;#177;&amp;#208;&amp;#189;&amp;#208;&amp;#184;&amp;#208;&amp;#186;&amp;#208;&amp;#190;&amp;#208;&amp;#178; (&amp;quot;Wizard Tournament&amp;quot;) is a fast-paced spell-shouting game of reaction in which players take on the roles of young wizards swinging their wands, casting spells, summoning magic crystals, and protecting themselves from the Dark Lord.&amp;#10;Each player starts the game with a magic wand, 5 crystals of one color of their choosing, and 1 crystal of each color that was not chosen for the game. &amp;#10;The game is played over a series of rounds. Each round, 2 dice are rolled. Die sides correspond to the colors of the magic crystals. Additionally, one die contains a white side and another die contains a black side. &amp;#10;Different combinations make different players cast certain spells (Attackus, Defendus, Captus, or Iamsafus), and whoever is the first to do it right either protects their crystals or gets a chance to take one from the opponent &amp;mdash; or even steal some from the Dark Lord himself!&amp;#10;Whenever one of the players has the majority in three crystal colors and doesn&amp;rsquo;t have the Dark Lord&amp;rsquo;s mark on them, the game is over and that player is declared the winner!&amp;#10;Count fast, be sure enough to cast your spells with a steady hand, and don&amp;rsquo;t let other wizards get ahead of you!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
